Draft complete. Alex Warren, typed **Enneagram 3 (The Achiever)**, built on verified quotes from the Jay Shetty interview and named third-party testimony.

**The thesis:** Fans see a grateful, faith-filled kid making feel-good anthems that tell everyone they'll be alright. The Type 3 lens reveals the opposite engine underneath. A boy who learned love had to be *earned* (pouring out his mother's bottles at nine, parenting his own siblings) now performs reassurance for millions because he can't feel it himself. The scoreboard hits #1 for ten weeks and never reaches the empty seat he's actually performing for: his dead parents' approval. He reads praise as gaslighting and hate as truth.

